<page api="js">
    <shortlink>grid component showGridColumn method</shortlink>
    <topic parent="{grid.object}" parentType="object" elementName="showGridColumn Method">{grid.object}.showGridColumn Method</topic>
    <description>Shows or hides a Grid column.</description>
    <prototype>{grid.Object}.showGridColumn(columnName, showHide)</prototype>
    <arguments>
        <argument>
            <name>columnName</name>
            <type>string</type>
            <description>The column name.</description>
        </argument>
        <argument>
            <name>showHide</name>
            <type>boolean</type>
            <description>*[js:false]* = hide column, *[js:true]* = show column.</description>
        </argument>
    </arguments>
    <discussion>
        <p>If 'showHide' is true, the column is shown (if it was hidden by a previous command that called this method to hide the column).</p>
    </discussion>
    <sections>
        <section>
            <title>Example</title>
            <description>If 'showHide' is false, the column is hidden. 'columnName' is the name of the column, and it must be UPPERCASE. Spaces in the 'columnName' must be replaced with underscores. For example, hide the 'LASTNAME' column.</description>
            <example code="js"><![CDATA[{grid.object}.showGridColumn('LASTNAME',false);]]></example>
        </section>
    </sections>
    <see>
        <ref link="grid%20components">Grid Component</ref>
        <ref link="Grid Component Properties and Methods">{grid.object}</ref>
    </see>
    <terms>grid component,column</terms>
</page> 